==English==
===Etymology===
First attested [[w:1910|1910]], from germanized [[Greek]] [[Schizophrenie]] "split mind", coined by [[w:Eugen Bleuler|Eugen Bleuler]], from {{Gr.}} [[schizo-]], from [[Ancient Greek]] [[σκίζω]] (''schizo'') "to tear, to split, to cut" + [[Ancient Greek]] prefix [[φρενο-]] 
"[[phreno-]]", from φρήν (''fren'') "mind, brain", from [[φρενόω]] (''freno-o'') "to make someone sensible".

===Pronunciation===
*[[AHD]]: [skĭt′səfrēnēə] or [skĭt′səfrĕnēə]

===Noun===
'''schizophrenia'''
# {{pathology}} A [[psychiatric]] [[diagnosis]] denoting a [[persistent]], often [[chronic]], mental illness variously affecting [[behavior]], [[thinking]], and [[emotion]].

